<subSubSection id="88916555ED517D75B688F8A9CF6178E6" pageId="12" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C03436DEED517D75B688F8A9CF6178E6" blockId="12.[712,1306,1794,2217]" lastBlockId="12.[98,1303,2223,3476]" pageId="12" pageNumber="93">
Previously included in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="078B4D5DED517D75B0DEF8A9CE3077A3" authorityName="F. Cuvier" authorityYear="1837" box="[1183,1305,1908,1941]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Allactaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Allactaga</taxonomicName>
and later Paralactaga, which has recently been found to be ajunior synonym of Scarturus. In the past, S. 
<taxonomicName id="078B4D5DED517D75B7A1F82ECF5E783A" baseAuthorityName="Argyropulo" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[992,1143,2035,2060]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Scarturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vinogradovi">vinogradovi</taxonomicName>
was considered a subspecies of S. 
<taxonomicName id="078B4D5DED517D75B055F7CFCF7E7805" baseAuthorityName="Lichtenstein" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[1044,1111,2066,2099]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Allactaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elater">elater</taxonomicName>
. Morphologically, it is in the subgenus Microallactaga, the sister group of subgenus Paralactaga. Genetically, S. 
<taxonomicName id="078B4D5DED517D75B7D2F755CF02789F" baseAuthorityName="Argyropulo" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[915,1067,2184,2217]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Scarturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vinogradovi">vinogradovi</taxonomicName>
issister to one of the genetic lineages from S. 
<taxonomicName id="078B4D5DED517D75B5B5F772C91178E6" baseAuthorityName="Lichtenstein" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[500,568,2223,2256]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Allactaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elater">elater</taxonomicName>
complex. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="88916555ED517D75B425F70BC9A67970" pageId="12" pageNumber="93" type="multiple">
<caption id="94F46656ED517D75B425F70BC9A67970" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6591985" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6591985" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6591985/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="93" startId="12.[100,254,2262,2295]" targetBox="[97,688,1799,2213]" targetPageId="12">
